name: Evelynn
title: Agony's Embrace
lore: Within the dark seams of Runeterra, the demon Evelynn searches for her next victim. She lures in prey with the voluptuous façade of a human female, but once a person succumbs to her charms, Evelynn's true form is unleashed. She then subjects her victim to unspeakable torment, gratifying herself with their pain. To the demon, these liaisons are innocent flings. To the rest of Runeterra, they are ghoulish tales of lust gone awry and horrific reminders of the cost of wanton desire.
blurb: Within the dark seams of Runeterra, the demon Evelynn searches for her next victim. She lures in prey with the voluptuous façade of a human female, but once a person succumbs to her charms, Evelynn's true form is unleashed. She then subjects her victim...
allytips: Allure's arm time might seem long, but the Charm and magic resist shred put Evelynn at an exteme advantage so are worth the wait.
While stealthed, pay attention to when you are (near) being detected by enemy champions. This is identified by the glowing yellow and red eyes over nearby enemy champions.
If at low health, you can take advantage of Demon Shade's healing and Camouflage to return to the fight and surprise opponents.
enemytips: Purchasing Vision Wards can help you detect Evelynn's location in order to prepare for her ambushes.
A large share of Evelynn's threat is in her charm, 'Allure.' Protect allies marked with 'Allure' or, if you are marked, make sure allies are between you and where Evelynn may attack from.
If you suspect Evelynn is about to ambush one of your teammates, let them know by pinging the minimap and typing in chat.

riot_spell_q.name: Hate Spike
riot_spell_q.description: Evelynn strikes out with her Lasher, dealing damage to the first unit hit. Then, Evelynn can shoot a line of spikes at nearby foes up to 3 times.
riot_spell_q.tooltip:
Evelynn's Lasher strikes in the target direction, dealing {{ e5 }} (+{{ a2 }}) magic damage to the first unit hit and causing Evelynn's next 3 spells or attacks on that unit deal {{ e4 }} (+{{ a1 }}) bonus magic damage. Then, Evelynn can recast this ability up to 3 times.

Recast: Fires spikes through the nearest enemy, dealing {{ e5 }} (+{{ a2 }}) magic damage to all units hit.

Refunds {{ e1 }}% of Hate Spike's cooldown if the Lasher hits a monster. Hate Spike prioritizes the target Evelynn is attacking.

riot_spell_w.name: Allure
riot_spell_w.description: Evelynn curses her target, causing her next attack or spell after a delay to charm her target and reduce their magic resist.
riot_spell_w.tooltip:
Curses target champion or monster for 5 seconds. If Evelynn hits the target with a basic attack or ability, she will expunge the Curse, refund its mana cost, and briefly slow the target by {{ e3 }}%.

If the Curse lasts at least 2.5 seconds, expunging it Charms the target for {{ e2 }} second(s) and:
  • Against champions: shreds Magic Resist by {{ e9 }}% for {{ e0 }} seconds.
  • Against monsters: deals {{ e7 }} (+{{ a1 }}) magic damage. Charm duration increased by {{ e1 }} seconds.
Casting Allure does not remove Evelynn from Demon Shade.

riot_spell_e.name: Whiplash
riot_spell_e.description: Evelynn whips her target with her Lasher, dealing damage. She then gains movement speed for a short duration.
riot_spell_e.tooltip:
Whip target with Lashers, applying on hit effects and dealing magic damage equal to {{ f1 }} plus {{ e5 }}% (+{{ a1 }}%) of their max health. Then, gain {{ e3 }}% movement speed for {{ e4 }} seconds.

Entering Demon Shade resets Whiplash's cooldown and empowers it. When empowered, Whiplash pulls Evelynn to her target, dealing magic damage to them and enemies in the way equal to {{ f2 }} plus {{ e6 }}% (+{{ a2 }}%) of their max health.

riot_spell_r.name: Last Caress
riot_spell_r.description: Evelynn briefly goes untargetable and decimates the area in front of her before warping backwards a long distance.
riot_spell_r.tooltip: Evelynn unleashes her demonic energy, becoming untargetable and decimating enemies in front of her. She then warps backwards. Deals {{ e1 }} (+{{ a1 }}) magic damage, increased to {{ f1 }} (+{{ f2 }}) to enemies below {{ e7 }}% health.

riot_spell_i.name: Demon Shade
riot_spell_i.description: When out of combat, Evelynn enters Demon Shade. Demon Shade heals Evelynn when she is low on health and grants Camouflage after level 6.

wikia_skill_i1.name: Demon Shade
wikia_skill_i1.blurb: When out of combat, Evelynn enters Demon Shade. Demon Shade heals Evelynn when she is low on health and grants Camouflage after level 6.
wikia_skill_i1.description: {{sbc|Innate:}} '''Evelynn''' gains ''Demon Shade'' after not taking damage from enemy champions or turrets for {{fd|1.5}} seconds, or after 4 seconds of [[basic attack]]ing or casting an ability.
wikia_skill_i1.description2: {{sbc|Demon Shade:}} While below {{as|{{sti|health|{{pp|250 to 590}} {{as|(+ 250% AP)}} health}}}}, '''Evelynn''' {{sti|healing|restores}} {{as|{{sti|health|{{pp|15 to 75}} health}}}} every second. From level 6 onward, ''Demon Shade'' also grants {{tip|camouflage}}.
wikia_skill_i1.notes:
* {{sbc|Lore:}} '''Evelynn''' has no need of disguises while she's invisible.
* Whenever ''Demon Shade'' activates a puff of purple smoke will trigger and a grey circle will appear around ''Evelynn'' and then she will start running differently.
* Whenever ''Evelynn'' approaches a visible enemy champion an eye will appear above them (only visible to her). This eye will change colors depending on how close ''Evelynn'' is to them.
** {{as|Yellow|energy}} means she is about to be spotted.
** {{as|Red|hp}} means she has been.
* When spotted, an exclamation mark will appear above ''Evelynn'' (only visible to her and her allies).
** ''Evelynn'' will not be spotted if the enemy doesn't have line of sight of her (e.g behind a turret or in the [[Sight|fog of war]]).
** She will be spotted by an enemy she has no sight of but ''Demon Shade's'' stealth will not break.
* The following can break ''Demon Shade's'' stealth:
** Certain [[summoner spell]]s ({{si|Exhaust}}, {{si|Heal}}, {{si|Ignite}}, {{si|Recall}}, {{si|Smite}}, {{si|Teleport}}).
** ''Evelynn'' herself capturing a neutral or enemy altar in {{tip|Twisted Treeline}} ({{as|red|hp}} eye for neutral and {{as|yellow|energy}} one for enemy but nevertheless she will be seen by enemies).

wikia_skill_q1.name: Hate Spike
wikia_skill_q1.blurb: Evelynn strikes out with her Lasher, dealing damage to the first unit hit. Then, Evelynn can shoot a line of spikes at nearby foes up to 3 times.
wikia_skill_q1.description: {{sbc|Dart:}} '''Evelynn''' flourishes her lashers, launching a dart in the target direction, dealing {{tip|magic damage|{{as|magic damage}}}} to the first enemy hit. Hitting a {{tip|monster}} refunds {{sti|cdr|60%}} of the cooldown.
wikia_skill_q1.description2: For the next 4 seconds, the enemy hit takes {{as|'''bonus''' magic damage}} from her next 3 [[basic attack]]s or abilities.
wikia_skill_q1.leveling2: {{st|Bonus Damage|{{ap|10 to 50}} {{as|(+ 25% AP)}}|Total Bonus Damage|{{ap|10*3 to 50*3}} {{as|(+ 75% AP)}}}}
wikia_skill_q1.description3: ''Hate Spike'' may be re-activated up to 3 times at no cost until the ability comes off cooldown.
wikia_skill_q1.description4: {{sbc|Spikes:}} '''Evelynn''' projects a line of spikes in the direction of her attack target, dealing {{as|magic damage}} to all enemies struck. ''Hate Spike'' will first prioritize '''Evelynn's''' attack target, then the nearest enemy champion.
wikia_skill_q1.leveling4: {{st|Spike Damage|{{ap|25 to 45}} {{as|(+ 30% AP)}}|Maximum Damage|{{ap|25*3 to 45*3}} {{as|(+ 90% AP)}}|Total Damage|{{ap|25*4+10*3 to 45*4+50*3}} {{as|(+ 195% AP)}}}}
wikia_skill_q1.customlabel: {{tt|Barrage Cooldown|The cooldown in between each spike cast. Is affected by cooldown reduction.}}
wikia_skill_q1.notes:
* ''Hate Spike'' prioritizes:
*# The last champion '''Evelynn''' hit
*# The last non-champion '''Evelynn''' hit
*# The lowest-health champion
*# The lowest-health non-champion
* Recasts can be buffered up to {{fd|0.5}} seconds before becoming castable.
* '''Evelynn''' has a minimum of 4 seconds to use the second casts regardless of the ability's cooldown, which is mainly only applicable versus monsters, on {{tip|Ultra Rapid Fire}} and in Training Mode.
* The ''Dart'' will apply {{tip|Single target}} effects, while the ''Spikes'' will apply {{tip|AoE}} effects.
* In {{tip|URF}} game mode, the spikes can be reactivated 10 times instead.

wikia_skill_w1.name: Allure
wikia_skill_w1.blurb: Evelynn curses her target, causing her next attack or spell after a delay to charm her target and reduce their magic resist.
wikia_skill_w1.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Evelynn''' ''curses'' the target champion or monster for 5 seconds.
wikia_skill_w1.description2: '''Evelynn's''' next basic attack or ability against the ''accursed'' ''expunges'' them, {{tip|slow|slowing}} them by 65%.
wikia_skill_w1.description3: ''Expunging'' a target will refund ''Allure's'' {{as|{{sti|mana|mana cost}}}}. If the target is ''cursed'' for at least {{fd|2.5}} seconds she also {{tip|charm|charms}} them, as well as applying additional effects based on the target type.
wikia_skill_w1.description4:
Against {{tip|champions}}, the ''expunge'' also {{sti|magic penetration|reduces}} their {{as|magic resistance}} for 4 seconds.
Against {{tip|monsters}}, the ''expunge'' deals {{as|'''bonus''' magic damage}} and the {{tip|charm}} lasts for 2 more seconds.
wikia_skill_w1.leveling4: {{st|Magic Resistance Reduction|{{as|{{ap|25 to 35}}%|magic resistance}}}}{{st|Bonus Magic Damage|{{ap|250 to 450}} {{as|(+ 60% AP)}}}}
wikia_skill_w1.notes:
* After {{fd|2.5}} seconds, the target sees an indicator that points toward her.
* The magic resistance shred will be applied to the attack or ability that procs it.

wikia_skill_e1.name: Whiplash
wikia_skill_e1.blurb: Evelynn whips her target with her Lasher, dealing damage. She then gains movement speed for a short duration.
wikia_skill_e1.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Evelynn''' whips the target enemy with her lashers, applying [[on-hit effects]] and dealing {{as|magic damage}}.
wikia_skill_e1.description2: '''Evelynn''' also gains {{sti|ms|{{as|30% '''bonus''' movement speed}}}} for 2 seconds.
wikia_skill_e1.leveling: {{st|Magic Damage|{{ap|55 to 115}} {{as|(+ 3% {{as|(+ {{fd|1.5}}% per 100 AP)}} of target's '''maximum''' health)}}}}
wikia_skill_e1.description3: Gaining {{ai|Demon Shade|Evelynn}} resets ''Whiplash's'' {{sti|cooldown}} and {{ai|Empowered Whiplash|Evelynn|empowers}} the next cast.
wikia_skill_e1.notes:
* ''Whiplash'' applies both {{tip|single target}} and {{tip|on-hit}} effects.
** The damage dealt by the ability itself is classified as ability damage, and will not apply [[life steal]]. Effects such as the on-hit physical damage from {{ii|Blade of the Ruined King}} will apply life steal to its own damage when inflicted by ''Whiplash''.

wikia_skill_e2.name: Empowered Whiplash
wikia_skill_e2.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Evelynn''' {{tip|dash|dashes}} toward the target enemy, dealing increased damage as well as damaging all enemies she passes through. ''On-hit effects are only applied to her target.''
wikia_skill_e2.leveling: {{st|Empowered Damage|{{ap|75 to 175}} {{as|(+ 4% {{as|(+ {{fd|2.5}}% per 100 AP)}} of target's '''maximum''' health)}}}}
wikia_skill_e2.description2: ''The {{as|percent health}} ratio deals a minimum of 25 damage and is capped at 450 against monsters.''
wikia_skill_e2.notes:
* ''Empowered Whiplash'' applies {{tip|AoE}} effects to secondary targets, but still applies {{tip|single target}} effects to her target.
* There is no time-out period on ''Empowered Whiplash''.

wikia_skill_r1.name: Last Caress
wikia_skill_r1.blurb: Evelynn briefly goes untargetable and decimates the area in front of her before warping backwards a long distance.
wikia_skill_r1.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Evelynn''' becomes {{tip|untargetable}} as she reveals her true form to all enemies in front of her, before {{tip|blink|blinking}} back 700 units.
wikia_skill_r1.description2: Enemies caught in her reveal are devastated, taking {{as|magic damage}}, doubled against enemies below {{as|{{sti|health|30% of their '''maximum''' health}}}}.
wikia_skill_r1.leveling2: {{st|Magic Damage|{{ap|125 to 375}} {{as|(+ 75% AP)}}|Empowered Damage|{{ap|125*2 to 375*2}} {{as|(+ 150% AP)}}}}
wikia_skill_r1.notes:
* ''Last Caress'' can be buffered during {{ai|Empowered Whiplash|Evelynn}}.
* The casting input controls the direction the damage is dealt, with the movement automatically happening in the reverse direction. This is comparable to {{ai|90 Caliber Net|Caitlyn}}.
* Enemies below the bonus damage threshold are marked with a giant pink kiss, but this does not indicate whether they are within the kill threshold.
